		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=707</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I woke up Wednesday at 3:30 am. As of midnight last night (Friday night), I had slept a broken 4 1/2 hours total. My body feels hazy; when I turn my head I get dizzy and I can&#8217;t seem to stomach any food. But last night I was able to eat a few Ravioli&#8217;s from <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=707">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I woke up Wednesday at 3:30 am. As of midnight last night (Friday night), I had slept a broken 4 1/2 hours total. My body feels hazy; when I turn my head I get dizzy and I can&#8217;t seem to stomach any food. But last night I was able to eat a few Ravioli&#8217;s from the casserole I made, and settle in at 3 am and drift off to wonderful sleep. I woke up so many times, but pushed the pain away and stayed so still in the darkness until my body relaxed and fell asleep again. I woke up this morning at 9. The sun was out and a cool breeze was coming through my window. I still feel&#8230; <em>off, b</em>ut I have a long day ahead and 6 hours is more sleep than the previous 2 nights and I&#8217;m thankful for every minute.<br />
Yesterday was&#8230;. eventful, frustrating and long. Two bit my head off for not going out of my way to force Three to his last basketball game of the season where Cede said he <em>MIGHT</em> show up. Three had already planned to have 3 of his friends from school sleep over. Cede usually remembers to call Three every month&#8230; sometimes every other month. He took time out of his schedule to visit him for 5 days last year. I&#8217;m not making him cancel plans with his friends at the last minute to see a person that doesn&#8217;t care about him in the least.<br />
I&#8217;m planning to go to the last game (he plays 2 today). I know I&#8217;ll be hurting for sitting through 1 game, but if your a <em>true</em> parent, you know that life isn&#8217;t about you.</p>
<p>I got up and made Three and his 3 friends french toast this morning. He&#8217;s happy and joking and beautiful. I look at him as I&#8217;m sure he looks at himself and wonder what is <em>so wrong</em> with him that Cede left him ( and me and his 2 brothers). What did he do to deserve such pain? I will make sure that I do everything in my power to help him be happy and ok with himself. He&#8217;s worth it to me. I&#8217;ll love him enough for 2 people, just like I do for his brothers. We&#8217;re ok. We&#8217;re more than ok, we&#8217;re great.</p>
<p><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D707&amp;linkname=Sleep%2C%20Anger%20and%20French%20Toast" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D707&amp;linkname=Sleep%2C%20Anger%20and%20French%20Toast" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_google_plus" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/google_plus?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D707&amp;linkname=Sleep%2C%20Anger%20and%20French%20Toast" title="Google+" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_pinterest" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/pinterest?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D707&amp;linkname=Sleep%2C%20Anger%20and%20French%20Toast" title="Pinterest" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd a2a_target addtoany_share_save" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D707&amp;title=Sleep%2C%20Anger%20and%20French%20Toast" id="wpa2a_2"></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
