		<item>
		<title>The Days go By</title>
		<link>http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=648</link>
		<pubDate>Sat, 31 Oct 2015 16:56:45 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brandyoldfashion]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Family Dynamic]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Cede]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Family]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=648</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[My father-in-law died this week. I hear he died of an aneurysm. I&#8217;ve known him since 1999 &#8211; 16 years now. Cede texted One, and One texted me so that I could tell Two and Three. I was shaken, but not as much as I thought I&#8217;d be. Neither were the kids. Almost 3 years <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=648">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My father-in-law died this week. I hear he died of an aneurysm. I&#8217;ve known him since 1999 &#8211; 16 years now. Cede texted One, and One texted me so that I could tell Two and Three. I was shaken, but not as much as I thought I&#8217;d be. Neither were the kids.<br />
Almost 3 years ago now, when Cede left, I went in person to my mother-in-law to let her know that Cede was having an affair and was not giving me any money for bills. I thought that I was close with her. We&#8217;ve never had a disagreement with her and never a single negative word was spoken back or forth. But as I was crying and telling her, she said, &#8220;I&#8217;m not getting involved.&#8221; I again, tried to explain to her that he had abandoned his children to be with another woman and he was NOT helping me with food or bills or anything. &#8220;I&#8217;m staying out of your life.&#8221;</p>
<p>&#8220;I&#8217;m staying out&#8230;&#8221; My children are her ONLY grandchildren. Most of the time through the last 13 years, I had been the one bringing over the kids to see their grandparents. Cede was either working or in the garage working on some car and was too busy to think about the relationship between his children and his parents. I made sure they were invited to each birthday. I made sure they knew about each milestone and accomplishment. And now my MIL was telling me that she was refusing to be a part of her daughter-in-law and grandchildren&#8217;s lives. I don&#8217;t understand the reasoning behind that.<br />
So, for the last few years, the kids have not seen them except for maybe once or twice a year for a few hours when Cede decided to bring the kids to them. They&#8217;ve completely missed out on everything that has happened with their grandkids. They have become strangers. And when my children heard that their grandpa had died, they weren&#8217;t really sad. They didn&#8217;t know him anymore.</p>
<p>If a daughter-in-law comes up to me some day and tells me that one of my sons is cheating on her and is refusing to give her any money for the kids, I will NOT be &#8220;staying out.&#8221; I will be marching over to that son&#8217;s house and beating him. That behavior IS NOT acceptable. That behavior is NOT what I taught them about responsibility.</p>
<p>So now they only have their grandma left. And they will sadly keep living without her in their life. They lost her years ago. It was her decision&#8230;. very sad&#8230; life is too short.</p>
<p><a class="a2a_button_facebook" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/facebook?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D648&amp;linkname=The%20Days%20go%20By" title="Facebook" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_twitter" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/twitter?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D648&amp;linkname=The%20Days%20go%20By" title="Twitter" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_google_plus" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/google_plus?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D648&amp;linkname=The%20Days%20go%20By" title="Google+" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_button_pinterest" href="http://www.addtoany.com/add_to/pinterest?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D648&amp;linkname=The%20Days%20go%20By" title="Pinterest" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"></a><a class="a2a_dd a2a_target addtoany_share_save" href="https://www.addtoany.com/share#url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brandyborges.com%2F%3Fp%3D648&amp;title=The%20Days%20go%20By" id="wpa2a_16"></a></p>]]></content:encoded>
