		<title>Just Daily Junk</title>
		<link>http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=636</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 23 Oct 2015 19:02:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Brandyoldfashion]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Family Dynamic]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health Issues]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Miscellaneous]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Cede]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Family]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Health]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[One]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Three]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Two]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=636</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I had a very low &#8220;low&#8221; that ran for a couple weeks. I&#8217;m not sure if there is a trigger, or 30 triggers, but I spiral downward. And I&#8217;m back up, I am fine&#8230; I just had to slap myself in the face and convince myself this is not the way I live. I get <a class="more-link" href="http://www.brandyborges.com/?p=636">Continue reading <i class="fa fa-chevron-right"></i></a>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I had a very low &#8220;low&#8221; that ran for a couple weeks. I&#8217;m not sure if there is a trigger, or 30 triggers, but I spiral downward. And I&#8217;m back up, I am fine&#8230; I just had to slap myself in the face and convince myself this is not the way I live.</p>
<p>I get mad that we don&#8217;t have enough to pay the electricity / water bill and Two ends up paying it so we can keep our power and water.<br />
I get mad that I cannot be a whole me and be the mother I want.<br />
I get mad that I can mearly bend at the right angle and my back goes out putting me in bed for 4 days.<br />
I get mad that there are still health issues and even my new doctor isn&#8217;t &#8220;hearing&#8221; me.<br />
I think I do ok fighting at things when it&#8217;s only 1 or 2, but when a pile piles on my shoulders, I crumble.</p>
<p>Families were made to have 2 parents and Cede is off having a great, kid-free life. And yes, he&#8217;s unconsciously missing every conversation, every story, every milestone, every corner of my kid&#8217;s life, but sometimes it just gets to me that he left me here to do things on my own. He doesn&#8217;t understand, and he&#8217;ll never be able to understand. I just have to accept it and move on.<span id="more-636"></span></p>
<p>So&#8230; let&#8217;s see. What has happened?<br />
Three had 80&#8217;s day at school. I had a great time dressing him up!<br />
The boys had a very fun teen activity. It was a scavenger hunt meets obstacle course type of thing.<br />
We (One, Two, Three and Dragonfly) went to a haunted house! It was Three&#8217;s first time. We had a blast and Three did GREAT!<br />
Two and I went to Milwaukee to pick up a shell for pieces for his Eagle Tallon.<br />
We then all went to the LaCrosse speedway so that he could race it.<br />
I&#8217;ve been working on moving the wall in the living room. One hung my drywall for me. I&#8217;ll have to get some pictures up of that.<br />
Three got his school pictures. He&#8217;s growing SO BIG!!</p>
<p>Also, today I finished the bench I&#8217;ve been working on. Three was home from school because of his hip and heal pain again, so he helped finish it and paint.<br />
The pictures of that are HERE.</p>
